The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Saturday, August 24, 2002 				 Eco funds 
																								Calcutta, Aug. 23 : The government will provide more funds to eco-clubs in schools involved in environment protection drives.																								Environment secretary Hirak Ghosh said money from the Centre has arrived and it would be distributed soon. Nearly 150 NGOs took part in a two-day camp in the city on environment concerns and means to combat the threat to the eco system. copy;  Copyrights 2002. All Rights Reserved. The Telegraph.  Conceptualised 
